    "# Node Response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:30:19.821947Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:30:19.821947Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:30:21.470729Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:30:21.470729Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:30:19.821947Z"
    },

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We load a suspension bridge model and visualize it:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:30:21.472738Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:30:21.471737Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.103906Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.102904Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:30:21.472738Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "opst.load_ops_examples(\"suspensionbridge\")  # or your model code here\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot\n",
    "opst.vis.pyvista.set_plot_props(notebook=True)  # set notebook=False for practical use\n",
    "fig = opst.vis.pyvista.plot_model(show_nodal_loads=True, show_ele_loads=True)\n",
    "fig.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")  # fig.show() for practical use"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Result Saving"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Next, we define gravity loads and perform the analysis\n",
    "The :func:`opstool.pre.gen_grav_load` function assists in generating gravity loads based on the current ``node masses``. \n",
    "Of course, you can define the loads in your own way."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.105907Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.104907Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.109858Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.109660Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.105907Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.timeSeries(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)\n",
    "_ = opst.pre.gen_grav_load(direction=\"Z\", factor=-9.81)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.110865Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.110865Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.125857Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.125857Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.110865Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.system(\"BandGeneral\")\n",
    "# Create the constraint handler, the transformation method\n",
    "ops.constraints(\"Transformation\")\n",
    "# Create the DOF numberer, the reverse Cuthill-McKee algorithm\n",
    "ops.numberer(\"RCM\")\n",
    "# Create the convergence test, the norm of the residual with a tolerance of\n",
    "# 1e-12 and a max number of iterations of 10\n",
    "ops.test(\"NormDispIncr\", 1.0e-12, 10, 3)\n",
    "# Create the solution algorithm, a Newton-Raphson algorithm\n",
    "ops.algorithm(\"Newton\")\n",
    "# Create the integration scheme, the LoadControl scheme using steps of 0.1\n",
    "ops.integrator(\"LoadControl\", 0.1)\n",
    "# Create the analysis object\n",
    "ops.analysis(\"Static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "``opstool`` allows us to save the data at each step of the analysis!\n",
    "First, we create a database class using :class:`opstool.post.CreateODB`, and then, during each step of the analysis, we call its method ``.fetch_response_step`` to retrieve the data for the current step. \n",
    "Once all the analysis steps are completed, we use the ``.save_response`` method to save the data in one go.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    ".. Note::\n",
    "    The data-saving method here is generic.\n",
    "    It enables saving all types of result data, including nodes, elements, and more, in one go. \n",
    "    Additionally, it is analysis-independent, functioning consistently for both static and dynamic analyses."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.126865Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.126865Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:30:24.344105Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:30:24.344105Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:30:23.126865Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  All responses data with _odb_tag = <span style=\"color: #008080; text-decoration-color: #008080; font-weight: bold\">1</span> saved in <span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">.opstool.output/RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">nc</span>!\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  All responses data with _odb_tag = \u001b[1;36m1\u001b[0m saved in \u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30mnc\u001b[0m!\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ODB = opst.post.CreateODB(odb_tag=1)\n",
    "for _ in range(10):\n",
    "    ops.analyze(1)\n",
    "    ODB.fetch_response_step()\n",
    "ODB.save_response()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Result Reading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "The provided function :func:`opstool.post.get_nodal_responses` make it easy to read node responses. Supported response types include:\n",
    "\n",
    "* \"disp\" - Displacement at the node.\n",
    "* \"vel\" - Velocity at the node.\n",
    "* \"accel\" - Acceleration at the node.\n",
    "* \"reaction\" - Reaction forces at the node.\n",
    "* \"reactionIncInertia\" - Reaction forces including inertial effects.\n",
    "* \"rayleighForces\" - Forces resulting from Rayleigh damping.\n",
    "* \"pressure\" - Pressure applied to the node.\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is saved as an \n",
    "`xarray.DataArray <https://docs.xarray.dev/en/stable/user-guide/data-structures.html>`_ structure, which facilitates more user-friendly data handling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Displacement"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   ]

    }

       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Loading disp response data from \u001b[1;38;2;28;199;208m.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;28;199;208m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;28;199;208mnc\u001b[0m \u001b[33m...\u001b[0m\n"
